    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the culture, style, and period associated with Tao-kuang in China during the Qing period (1644-1911). The style is characterized by rose-colored enamel ware, typically bearing the six character mark of emperor K'ang-hsi.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
